stylometry: You determine the total cost of managing inventory by balancing how much inventory to order, while minimizing the number of orders, and how much inventory to have, while minimizing the holding costs. It costs businesses every time they order inventory but it also cost them to hold on to it when it is not needed, but there are also cost of running out of inventory and possible losing customers. This is done using the EOQ model that looks at reorder costs and the holding costs.
